Prog conventions 

1. main.h
/*THIS file contains all the info related to registers, timers, OSC freq ,typedefs and interrupts */

2. File.h
/*THIS file contains only  global variables , function prototypes ,  no other header file should ever be included in this header file . Ever. */

3.main.c
/*
Should always be of this format when including files

 "Main.h"
 "Port.h"
 "Simple_EOS.h"	// Or any other OS file

 "File1.h"
 ...

*/

4.file.c
/*
Should primarily include with 
main.h
port.h

then with the file header
file.h
otherfileheaders.h

*/
